Iteration 15 - probe-disabled dispatch regression closure
Date: 2026-05-21 (Asia/Taipei)

Root cause fixed:
- services/nodepool/cmd/server/main.go
- dispatch only used ACTIVE worker list even when probe was disabled.
- In regression path (probe fail then probe disabled), no candidate remained and dispatch failed.

Fix:
- when `NODEPOOL_PRE_DISPATCH_PROBE=false` and ACTIVE list is empty, fallback to `ListWorkers(includeOffline=true)`.

Verification:
1) go test ./cmd/server -run TestMasterNode_DispatchTaskToWorker_PreDispatchProbe -count=1
   - PASS
2) python scripts/one_click_failover_check.py --mode single --admin-user worker1 --admin-pass worker123 --task-user worker1 --task-pass worker123
   - PASS
3) python scripts/one_click_failover_check.py --mode failover --admin-user worker1 --admin-pass worker123 --task-user worker1 --task-pass worker123 --timeout-sec 60
   - PASS
   - victim transitioned to OFFLINE after bad-address injection
   - step2 dispatched to alternate worker

Iteration 16 - reliability harness pre-clean for stable simulated user flow
Date: 2026-05-21 (Asia/Taipei)

Root cause fixed:
- scripts/reliability_harness.py
- Previous calibration run could inherit stale local listeners and stale worker registry state from earlier manual stacks.
- This produced false negatives (`no live worker available to kill`, stuck long task, zombie offline worker).

Fix:
- Added `cleanup_conflicting_ports(run_dir)` before harness dependencies/services startup.
- Windows path: parse `netstat -ano` and `taskkill /PID /F` listeners on harness-critical ports.
- Evidence recorded in run-local `preclean.log`.

